Usage: reportPinAssignStatistics [-help] [-outFile <pin_qor_file_name>] [-hinst <hinstNameList> | -ptn <ptnNameList> ] [ -maxFanOut <fan_out_count> ] [ -maxRegisterFanOut <register_fan_out_count> ]

-help                            # Prints out the command usage
-hinst <hinstNameList>           # list of partition hinst names. QoR will be
                                 # computed for all pins of these hinst.
                                 # Default: all partition and clone hinsts
                                 # (string, optional)
-maxFanOut <fan_out_count>       # QoR report will not be generated for pins if
                                 # the number of instances in the timing cone
                                 # fanout of this pin exceeds this max fan out
                                 # count. Default: 1000 (string, optional)
-maxRegisterFanOut <register_fan_out_count>
                                 # QoR report will not be generated for pins if
                                 # the number of registers in the timing cone
                                 # fanout of this pin exceeds this max fan out
                                 # count. Default: 50 (string, optional)
-outFile <pin_qor_file_name>     # QoR data will be output in this file.
                                 # Default: ./pin_qor.txt (string, optional)
-ptn <ptnNameList>               # list of partition names. QoR will be
                                 # computed for all pins of these partitions.
                                 # Default: all partitions (and clones)
                                 # (string, optional)